
- After any functional code change:
  - For Ruby/Rails changes:
    - Add or update unit tests in `apps/rails/spec/models/` for model changes
    - Add or update controller tests in `apps/rails/spec/controllers/` for controller changes
    - Add or update system tests in `apps/rails/spec/system/` for UI flow changes
    - Run tests with `bundle exec rspec <path_to_spec>` to verify
  - For TypeScript/Next.js changes:
    - Add or update unit tests for front-end business logic

- After any functional code change:
  - For Ruby/Rails changes:
    - Add or update unit tests in `apps/backend/spec/models/` for model changes
    - Add or update controller tests in `apps/backend/spec/controllers/` for controller changes
    - Add or update system tests in `apps/backend/spec/system/` for UI flow changes
    - Run tests with `bundle exec rspec <path_to_spec>` to verify
  - For TypeScript/Next.js changes:
    - Add or update unit tests for front-end business logic